Example:
```typespec
model Result {
  @visibility(Lifecycle.Read)
  id: string;
  @visibility(Lifecycle.Read)
  status: string;
  // This property will NOT appear in the response
  @visibility(Lifecycle.Create)
  secret: string;
}

@route("/result")
interface Results {
  @get getResult(): Result;
}
```
In this example, only 'id' and 'status' will be present in the response schema, and both will be marked as readOnly in OpenAPI. No additional visibilityFilter is required.

